v0.1.4: host_network mode to reach LAN MQTT broker

In bridge-network mode (host_network: false) some HA OS installs can't
route from the add-on container to certain LAN hosts even though HA core
itself can reach them. Observed: the add-on reached a Shelly device fine
but couldn't reach an MQTT broker on the same subnet — TCP SYN went
unanswered.

Switching to host_network: true makes the add-on share the HA host's
network namespace, which is the same path HA core uses for its own MQTT
integration. Trade-off is loss of network isolation between the add-on
and the host, which is acceptable for a single-user LAN tool.

